SIMPLE: ocular
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ocular
<hw>Oc"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ocularis</ets>, <ets>ocularius</ets>, fr. <ets>oculus</ets> the
eye: cf. F. <ets>oculaire</ets>. See <er>Eye</er>, and cf.
<er>Antler</er>, <er>Inveigle</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Depending
on, or perceived by, the eye; received by actual sight; personally
seeing or having seen; <as>as, <ex>ocular</ex> proof</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thomas was an <qex>ocular</qex> witness of Christ's death.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the eye;
optic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ocular</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ocular
<hw>Oc"u*lar</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>The eyepiece of
an optical instrument, as of a telescope or microscope.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ocularly</ent>⟦br⟧
